Short description: when a plugin registers a collection of "ContentTypeSearchDescriptor"s these are shown in the "Type" section in the left column to restrict the search, but if choosing such a type defined by a plugin the search results are not restricted to the choosen type.
This problem only appears when the "Confluence Search Plugin" is active. When deactivating this plugin the "standard search" is shown which fully supports adding content types.

Steps to reproduce:
- add a SiteSearchPluginModule like
{code}
import com.atlassian.confluence.search.plugin.ContentTypeSearchDescriptor;
import com.atlassian.confluence.search.plugin.SiteSearchPluginModule;
import com.atlassian.confluence.search.v2.SearchQuery;
import com.atlassian.confluence.search.v2.query.LabelQuery;

/**
 * Add some label as "content type" to filter the search.
 */
public class ByLabelSiteSearchPluginModule implements SiteSearchPluginModule
{

    @Override
    public Collection<ContentTypeSearchDescriptor> getContentTypeDescriptors() 
    {
        Collection<ContentTypeSearchDescriptor> descriptors = new ArrayList<ContentTypeSearchDescriptor>();
        // just for testing: add a single label
        descriptors.add(new ByLabelSearchDescriptor("advanced"));
        return descriptors;
    }

    public static class ByLabelSearchDescriptor implements ContentTypeSearchDescriptor
    {
        private final String label;

        public ByLabelSearchDescriptor(String label)
        {
            this.label = label;
        }

        @Override
        public SearchQuery getQuery()
        {
            return new LabelQuery(label);
        }

        @Override
        public String getIdentifier()
        {
            return "byLabel_" + label;
        }

        @Override
        public String getI18NKey()
        {
            return org.apache.commons.lang3.StringUtils.capitalize(label) + " pages";
        }

        @Override
        public boolean isIncludedInDefaultSearch()
        {
            return false;
        }
    }
}
{code} (This component adds a dummy "content type", which should restrict the search to all pages having the label "advanced")
- register this class as a component in some atlassian-plugin.xml, e.g. {code}    <site-search name="By Label Site Search" key="byLabelSiteSearch" class="my.company.testcode.ByLabelSiteSearchPluginModule">
        <description>Test: Add label-types to Confluence site search</description>
    </site-search>{code}
- install this plugin in some confluence instance
- log in to the confluence UI and trigger some search (e.g. with the standard demonstration space installed search for "Advanced")
- on the search result page notice that there is an "Advanced pages" type in the left column
- clicking on that link adds a parameter {{type=byLabel_advanced}} to the URL

Expected behaviour
- search results are restricted to pages with the label "advanced" (beside of containing the search term)

Observed behaviour:
- search result is the same as without choosing the "Advanced pages" content types 

This problem only occurs if the Search plugin (Add-on key: {{com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.search.confluence-search}}) is installed and active.
Version of the plugin: 1.2.22
It only affects types defined by plugins; the preinstalled content types ("pages", "blog posts", "attachments" work fine). 

Either the plugin should not show the content types registered by plugins in the "Type" section as options, or it should not ignore them in the query.

